1 (4) “CHILD WELFARE CASEWORKER” MEANS A HUMAN SERVICES
2 PROFESSIONAL WHO MEETS THE QUALIFICATIONS FOR EMPLOYMENT UNDER §
3 4–301 OF THE HUMAN SERVICES ARTICLE.
4 [(3)] (5) “Citation” means a charging document, other than an
5 indictment, an information, or a statement of charges, issued to a defendant by a peace
6 officer or other person authorized by law to do so.
7 [(4)] (6) “Educator” means a principal, vice–principal, teacher, or
8 teacher’s aide at a public or private preschool, elementary, or secondary school.
9 [(5)] (7) “Emergency services personnel” means:
10 (i) A career firefighter of a county or municipal corporation;
11 (ii) An emergency medical services provider as defined in § 13–516
12 of the Education Article of a county or municipal corporation;
13 (iii) A rescue squad employee of a county or municipal corporation;
14 and
15 (iv) A volunteer firefighter, rescue squad member, or advanced life
16 support unit member of a county or municipal corporation.
17 [(6)] (8) “Indictment” means a charging document returned by a grand
18 jury and filed in circuit court.
19 [(7)] (9) “Information” means a charging document filed in court by a
20 State’s Attorney.
21 [(8)] (10) “Law enforcement officer” means:
22 (i) A law enforcement officer as defined in § 1–101 of the Public
23 Safety Article;
24 (ii) The Police Commissioner of Baltimore City;
25 (iii) An individual who serves at the pleasure of the Police
26 Commissioner of Baltimore City;
27 (iv) The police chief of a county law enforcement agency;
28 (v) The police chief of a municipal corporation;

